      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "FLYING MAVERICK (4) was strongly fancied latest and proved too good with a 3.5 lengths win at Ballarat in a handy 21.94. Jumping from the pinch draw but goes well over this trip. Well placed and will be tough to beat. MR. KIA ORA (2) jumped from the rails and recorded an upset win in a Mix 3/4 last time, scoring by 0.8 lengths at Shepparton (22.08). Has a strong winning record here at this journey. Recorded one of the quickest times on the card in scoring last start. Looks a key chance if runs up to latest figure. WAXING (8) has a strong record this trip with six wins and four placings from 15 starts. Missed the frame latest (22.70) when fourth over 390m at Warrnambool in a Grade 5. Looks a key chance on best figures. BULL DURHAM (6) generally performs well here at this distance.",
